# Enrollify UI layout

## Site container (Tailwind v4)

Do **not** define `.container` in `@layer components`. Tailwind v4 emits `@utility container { width: 100% }` in the utilities layer, which overrides component-layer width calc and removes mobile gutters.

**Canonical definition:** [`src/index.css`](../src/index.css) — single `@utility container` with `padding-inline` gutters:

```css
@utility container {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: var(--container-max);
  margin-inline: auto;
  padding-inline: 1.25rem;

  @variant md { padding-inline: 3rem; }
  @variant lg { padding-inline: 3.75rem; }
}
```

- Do not nest `@utility` inside `@media` — use `@variant` instead (build fails otherwise).
- Page sections use `className="container mx-auto"` via [`Section.tsx`](../src/components/ui/Section.tsx) or directly in layout/hero.
- `<main>` has no horizontal padding — children must use `.container`.

## Mobile navigation overlay

[`MobileNav.tsx`](../src/components/layout/MobileNav.tsx) must portal the open overlay to `document.body`:

```tsx
{overlay ? createPortal(overlay, document.body) : null}
```

**Why:** [`Navbar.tsx`](../src/components/layout/Navbar.tsx) uses `backdrop-blur-sm` on `<header>`. `backdrop-filter` creates a containing block — inline `position: fixed` overlays are trapped to header height (~180px) instead of the viewport.

Drawer panel: `h-dvh`, safe-area padding (`env(safe-area-inset-top/bottom)`), `z-50` overlay.

## Logo sizing

[`Logo.tsx`](../src/components/ui/Logo.tsx) — use `variant="nav"` in navbar (`h-10 sm:h-12`), `variant="footer"` in footer. Never use full `h-[140px]` in the sticky header.

## Pre-merge checks (390px viewport)

```js
document.querySelector('#hero h1')?.getBoundingClientRect().left  // expect ~20
// Open menu — overlay parent height should match innerHeight, not header height
```
